Lucky girl syndrome ✨ have you guys seen the viral videos on this? basically you’re telling yourself you are the luckiest girl and training your mind to look for good things, even little moments, and as they happen saying “I’m so lucky everything goes my way.”

NOT to be confused with toxic positivity that everything is perfect but training your mind to look for the good and acknowledge good things as they happen. almost feels like a form of gratitude just worded different. 

one of the videos that popped in my feed talked about how this is so much bigger than affirmations because in order to rewire your brain it needs an EXPERIENCE to pair with it over just words. I liked that concept, because sometimes I feel really cheesy saying affirmations so I don’t do them a lot 😂 but I like how this is just a part of your day. (im going to share her video in my stories it was really good) 

So when you get the front row parking spot or get your kids out the door for school on time “I’m so lucky everything goes my way” when you get a table at your favorite restaurant, “everything works out for me”. Big or small recognize the moments. 

At the simplest I think lucky girl syndrome trains your mind to focus on the blessings and gratitude, and even when your having hard days knowing that good things are always coming your way ❤️ 

who else is starting their lucky girl era with me?

Last minute easy Mother’s Day gift idea or keepsake for yourself 🙊 Im obsessed with any way to freeze and remember these little moments with the kids. How sweet are these handprint prints 🥺 

HOW TO: 
Just put your hand over your kids and photo copy it. I liked fingers together more than spread apart but your choice :) 

If you want black background like ours, I put a black sweatshirt overtop our hands for contrast. If you want white background just leave the top of copier open. 

Print it out and you can frame the paper (we used an 8x10 frame from target just had to trim paper down a little) or you can also scan it and print it on a smaller photo paper like a 5x7. I wanted the life size hand prints so that’s why I kept the regular paper ❤️

Tip: you can also do this with grandparents hand and it would make a sweet gift for them or you could use print as the front of a Mother’s Day card for grandparent. I personally lovvvve homemade gifts more than anything so these little mementos are always super special to me. 

Tip 2: write name and age or year on back so when you find later you remember age ❤️

For easy reference- save this post for later ✨ would love to see all your handprint art. 

Thanks @melissametrano for the idea to do this ❤️ #momlife #kidscrafts #motherhood #studiomcgee #giftidea

3 timeless ways to style a blazer for fall ✨🤍 sharing tips below 👇🏼 

🤍 Layer it over an all black look with loafers. have been kind of nervous to try the loafer look but I love how they tied the look together for a cool 90s sophisticated feel. I did black socks instead of white felt like it unified the look a little more. how are you guys feeling about loafers? 

🤍 Pair it with a dark straight leg denim for fall. The darker wash denim is everything this season and a classic blazer and ankle boot is a timeless way to style it. Don’t forget a belt to complete the look. 

🤍 The beauty of an oversized blazer is being able to double as a dress. It’s a surprisingly versatile look that you can pair with loafers or boots for a more sophisticated look or your favorite sneakers and a hat for a cool casual vibe.  Also  I wear biker shorts or a short skirt underneath :)

ice-skating in NYC tips ❄️

⛸️ Bryant park is free! (with reservations - book online) you just pay to rent skates vs Rockefeller which is $21-73 per person + skates). Bryant park is also one of the largest ice skating rinks in nyc so there’s lots of room. 

🎄 they have a holiday market around the rink highly suggest going even if you don’t skate. We got Christmas ornaments as souvenirs and had one of the best hot chocolates I’ve ever had. Also really like the chicken noodle soup bowls. 

🤍 you can’t take any bags on rink, and have to pay to check bags so I’d say don’t bring a purse. I wore a coat with good size pockets for my phone and small belongings :) 

🐧if you have toddlers rent the penguin so it’s easier for them. We went with Beckham at the same age Ollie was (and didn’t rent it) and I feel like ollie skated way more and had a better time because he could stand up better. 

📆 go on a weekday. If it’s feasible with your schedule. Highly recommend way less crowds.  mornings and early afternoon they said are best times and least crowded. 

❄️ ice skating was one of my favorite things we did on the trip. there’s lots of rinks around the city: Central Park, Rockefeller, Bryant park, Hudson yards, and I’ve heard they opened a new ice skating rink under Brooklyn bridge that looks really pretty too 🥰 but if you’re in nyc think it’s a must do!

NYC during the holidays 🤩🎄❄️ it’s just magical
